President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Aprille Joy Ericsson as Assistant Secretary of Defense (Science and Technology) at the Department of Defense. Ericsson currently serves as the New Business Lead at NASA's Goddard Space Flight Center and has over 30 years of experience at NASA in various leadership positions. She has a strong background in Astrophysics, Heliophysics, Planetary, and Earth Science, and has been involved in missions such as the James Webb Space Telescope and lunar orbiters. Ericsson is also a champion for the advancement of women and people of color in STEM fields and has received numerous awards and honors for her work.

Additionally, President Biden intends to nominate John N. Nkengasong as Ambassador-At-Large for Global Health Security and Diplomacy at the Department of State. Nkengasong currently serves as the Ambassador-At-Large and Coordinator of U.S Government Activities to Combat HIV/AIDS Globally and Special Representative for Global Health Diplomacy at the Department of State. If confirmed, Nkengasong would lead the new Bureau of Global Health Security and Diplomacy, focusing on global health security and diplomacy, as well as the U.S. President's Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR). Nkengasong has a strong background in public health and has held various leadership positions, including Director of the Africa Centres for Disease Control and Prevention. He has received several awards and recognitions for his work in global health.

Both Ericsson and Nkengasong have impressive educational backgrounds and extensive experience in their respective fields.